Treasury Deputy Neal Wolin Met With Karzai on Afghanistan Trip

-- B y   I a n   K a t z
-- 
2011-02-17T18:49:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/treasury-deputy-neal-wolin-met-with-karzai-on-afghanistan-trip.html
U.S. Deputy Treasury Secretary Neal Wolin met with Afghan President  Hamid Karzai  to discuss  Afghanistan ’s financial sector during a visit to Kabul that
ended today.  Wolin met with Karzai and other government officials to
talk about “the importance of Afghan efforts to reform and
strengthen its financial sector, and stressed the need for the
Afghan government to take swift and decisive action to ensure a
credible, effective resolution of issues related to Kabul
Bank,” the Treasury Department said in a statement today.  Wolin visited Kabul today and yesterday, the Treasury said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Katz in Washington at 
 ikatz2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
